🏦 Week — OOP Weekend Project: Bank Branch System
Goal: Build a simulated bank branch in Python using Object-Oriented Programming.
You'll build 4 classes:

BankAccount — the base account with deposit, withdraw, and balance
SavingsAccount — inherits from BankAccount, adds an apply_interest method
Customer — has a name and a list of accounts, can open new ones
Bank — manages all customers, can add/find customers and report total funds held

Requirements:

A customer can hold multiple accounts
Withdrawals should not allow the balance to go negative — print a warning if attempted
The Bank class should be able to print a summary: each customer and their total balance
SavingsAccount.apply_interest(rate) should increase the balance by a percentage (e.g. 5% → balance × 1.05)

Stretch goals (if you finish early):

Add a TransactionHistory to BankAccount that logs every deposit and withdrawal
Add a transfer(amount, target_account) method between two accounts

Deliverable: A single bank.py file. At the bottom, write a small script that creates a bank, adds 2–3 customers, opens accounts, makes transactions, and prints the summary.